        <section class="policy-section" id="section-1">
          <div class="section-label">01</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">How to Delete Your Account</h2>
          <p>Deleting your account is simple and can be done directly from within the app. Follow these steps:</p>
          <ul class="policy-list">
            <li>Open the <strong>Doodh Mandi</strong> app on your device</li>
            <li>Sign in to your account with your phone number</li>
            <li>Navigate to your <strong>Profile</strong> section</li>
            <li>Scroll down to find <strong>Delete Account</strong> option</li>
            <li>Tap on <strong>Delete Account</strong></li>
            <li>Review the confirmation message carefully</li>
            <li>Confirm the deletion request by tapping <strong>Yes, Delete Permanently</strong></li>
          </ul>
          <div class="info-callout">
            <span class="callout-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="7" stroke="#27ae60" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M8 7v4M8 5v.5" stroke="#27ae60" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
            </span>
            Once confirmed, your account deletion process will begin immediately. This action <strong>cannot be undone</strong>.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section" id="section-2">
          <div class="section-label">02</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">What Data Will Be Deleted</h2>
          <p>When you delete your account, the following information will be <strong>permanently removed</strong> from our systems within 30 days:</p>
          <ul class="policy-list">
            <li>Your full name</li>
            <li>Phone number</li>
            <li>Email address (if provided)</li>
            <li>Shop or business name</li>
            <li>Business details and profile information</li>
            <li>Complete order history and transaction records</li>
            <li>Device token (FCM token) for push notifications</li>
            <li>Account settings and preferences</li>
            <li>All associated account data</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="info-callout">
            <span class="callout-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><circle cx="8" cy="8" r="7" stroke="#27ae60" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M8 7v4M8 5v.5" stroke="#27ae60" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
            </span>
            Your data is irreversibly deleted and cannot be recovered after 30 days. Please ensure you have backed up any important information before proceeding.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section" id="section-3">
          <div class="section-label">03</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Data That May Be Retained</h2>
          <p>
            Certain information may be retained for limited periods only when required by applicable laws, regulations, fraud prevention, dispute resolution, or security purposes.
          </p>
          <ul class="policy-list">
            <li>Transaction records required for tax or legal compliance (kept for the period mandated by Indian law)</li>
            <li>Data needed to prevent fraud or resolve disputes between suppliers and retailers</li>
            <li>Security logs for account protection and system security</li>
            <li>Aggregated, anonymized data for app analytics and improvements</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Any retained information is kept only for the minimum period required and is stored securely with access restricted to authorized personnel only.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section" id="section-4">
          <div class="section-label">04</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Important Notes</h2>
          <ul class="policy-list">
            <li><strong>No Reactivation:</strong> Your account cannot be reactivated after deletion. You will need to create a new account if you wish to use Doodh Mandi again.</li>
            <li><strong>Account Name Cannot Be Reused:</strong> Your phone number cannot be used to register a new account for <strong>90 days</strong> after deletion.</li>
            <li><strong>Outstanding Orders:</strong> Ensure all outstanding orders are settled before deleting your account.</li>
            <li><strong>Outstanding Payments:</strong> Any pending payments or disputes must be resolved before deletion.</li>
            <li><strong>Processing Time:</strong> Complete deletion of all data takes up to 30 days. Some cached data may remain temporarily.</li>
            <li><strong>No Refunds:</strong> We do not provide refunds for deleted accounts. Payment terms remain as per our Terms & Conditions.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

